<!--
  Shape-drift fixture (#78): a valid RSS 2.0 feed whose items still have a <link>
  (so they parse and get a guid) but whose <title> element was renamed/removed in
  a source redesign. parseRss20 keeps each item but with title: '' — a parse that
  "succeeded" yet produced junk. The 'missing_required_fields' anomaly (field:
  title). Both items parse, so this is NOT a zero/drop case — it exercises the
  per-item required-field validation distinctly.
-->
